introduction: Overview (3)Born	June 12, 1983 in Beverly Hills, California, USABirth Name	Parisse Ashley BootheHeight	5' 9" (1.75 m)Mini Bio (1)Parisse Boothe was born in Beverly Hills to Pamela and Powers Boothe. Graduating high school after only three years, she attended college at the University of Oregon, majoring in Theatre Arts. She was nationally awarded in the American College Theatre Festival. Upon moving back to Los Angeles, she began work on the Emmy-winning HBO series, Deadwood (2004), as the Bella Union prostitute,"Tess". After work on the hit series, Parisse began working in film, starring amidst Sean Astin and James Gammon in the baseball classic, The Final Season (2007); and others. She consistently shows her diversity from motion capture, television, film, producing and directing.- IMDb Mini Biography By: Peter MasonTrivia (7)Daughter of Powers Boothe.Parisse's was name was inspired by legendary actress Cyd Charisse and Parisse's conception in Paris, France.Attended the University of Oregon as a Theater Arts major.Graduated from Colin McEwen High School in Malibu, California, as Salutatorian and was inducted as a member of the National Collegiate Honor Society.Owner of Queen B Pictures.Attended the University of Oregon.Sister of Preston Boothe.
